<p>I am installing Open MPI v1.8.8 with CUDA v7.5 on my Linux Debian. I have tested CUDA and it works, tested OpenMPI and it works too. But when i try to combine them into a program, i meet an error: cannot find cuda.h file . This is my scenario:</p>  <p>My program source code include these .h file</p>  <p><code>include "cuda.h" include "mpi.h"</code></p>  <p>I run command:  <code>mpicc &lt;filePath&gt; -o test</code> <code> And error appear:</code>cuda.h: No such file or directory  #include "cuda.h"`</p>  <p>omp_info give me :     <code>mca:mpi:base:param:mpi_built_with_cuda_support:value:false</code></p>  <p>I have googled , and i followed some methods i found:  <code>./configure --with-cuda</code> <code>./configure --with-cuda=/usr/local/cuda-7.5</code> ( source link : <a href="http://mirror.its.dal.ca/openmpi/faq/?category=buildcuda" rel="nofollow">http://mirror.its.dal.ca/openmpi/faq/?category=buildcuda</a>) After that, i remake all , remake install Open Mpi. I run: mpicc or mpirun, the compiler give me error : <code>mpirun error mca: base: component find: unable to open /usr/local/lib/openmpi/mca_mpool_sm</code></p>  <p>I set up soft link : <code>ln -s /usr/local/cuda/include /usr/include</code> ( describe in link : <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30607733/building-cuda-aware-openmpi-on-ubuntu-12-04-cannot-find-cuda-h">Building CUDA-aware openMPI on Ubuntu 12.04 cannot find cuda.h</a>). But it cannot fix my issue.</p>  <p>Does anyone successfully install it? Please help me or share your experience. Thanks.</p>